snippet.textDisplay: Being a female isn't about having long hair or painted nails or wearing "girly" clothes. It's not about playing with Barbies when you're young, or taking care of baby dolls either. It's in the DNA. And no matter how much make up you put on or how long your hair is or how many times you paint your nails, your DNA is male. You cannot know what it is like to be a woman because you are not one. Dress how you like. Get your hair done how you please. I don't care about any of that or judge you negatively for it. But don't expect society at large to tell an outright lie (ie that you are in fact an actual female) to make you feel better about it all.
